Privacy Policy
(Last Updated June 27, 2018)
For users residing in Asia* (except Japan and South Korea)
The Pokémon Company, and its affiliates, Pokémon Center Co. Ltd., The Pokémon Company International, Inc., and Pokémon Korea Inc. (collectively “we,” “us,” “our,” “the Company”), are committed to the protection of your information. We have written this privacy policy (“Privacy Policy”) to describe what information we collect during your use of Pokémon Quest (“the App”), why we collect it, how we use it, and under what circumstances we might disclose it.
This Privacy Policy and the
terms of use
(“Terms”) govern your use of the App. By downloading and using the App, you consent to the Terms and Privacy Policy. If you are a minor in your country of residence, you acknowledge that your parent/guardian has reviewed and consents to your use of the App subject to the Terms and this Privacy Policy. If you or your parent/guardian do not agree with the Terms or Privacy Policy, do not use the App.
This Privacy Policy applies only to information submitted and collected via the App, and does not apply to information that may be collected by us offline. Additionally, this Privacy Policy applies only to the App, and we are not responsible for the content or activities provided on linked or affiliates’ services, apps, or websites. Once you have clicked on an advertisement or other link and have left the App, our Privacy Policy no longer applies. Please read the privacy policy at the redirected location to see how your information will be handled.
